llaborates with Georgia Tech professor Charlie Kemp on using the <a href=\"http://www.willowgarage.com/blog/2011/07/13/robots-humanity\" target=\"_blank\">Willow Garage</a>  PR2 robot as a surrogate, as well as Chad Jenkins&#39; <a href=\"http://brown-robotics.org/wp/\" target=\"_blank\">RLAB</a>  at Brown on quadrotors for expanding range of motion. </p><p>As the Willow Garage blog post says: &quot;Every day, people take for granted the simple act of scratching an itch. In Henry&#39;s case, 2-3 times every hour of every day he gets an itch he can&#39;t scratch. With the aid of a PR2, Henry was able to scratch an itch for himself for the first time in 10 years.&quot;</p>"}],"speaker_name":"Henry Evans and Chad Jenkins","tags":["TEDx","culture","disability","technology"],"title":"Meet the robots for humanity","video_type":{"id":"2","name":"TEDx Talk"},"viewed_count":1223296}]}
